WEBVTT

00:07.200 --> 00:08.767
[Tape player clicks]

00:08.800 --> 00:11.767
Michel:
The Catastrophe.

00:11.800 --> 00:14.467
The War of 1948,

00:14.500 --> 00:16.933
if it can
be called a war,

00:16.967 --> 00:20.267
when your British
betrayed us

00:20.300 --> 00:24.033
and the Zionists drove us
out of our homeland.

00:24.067 --> 00:29.633
When I was 8,
I was driven from our land.

00:29.667 --> 00:33.167
When I was 10, I joined Ashbal
with my brothers.

00:33.200 --> 00:34.167
Kurtz:
"Brothers."

00:34.200 --> 00:35.367
[Tape player clicks]

00:35.400 --> 00:37.000
[Reel rewinding]

00:37.033 --> 00:39.167
[Tape player clicks]

00:39.200 --> 00:42.833
Michel: When I was 10, I joined
Ashbal with my brothers.

00:42.867 --> 00:44.367
See?
[Tape player clicks]

00:44.400 --> 00:46.167
Brothers.

00:46.200 --> 00:47.333
It's not enough.

00:47.367 --> 00:49.333
It sounds like Salim.

00:49.367 --> 00:51.833
**

00:51.867 --> 00:54.633
The revolutionary crowd.

00:54.667 --> 00:58.033
**

00:58.067 --> 01:01.333
Who is this?

01:01.367 --> 01:03.433
2312.

01:03.467 --> 01:04.967
Charmian Ross.

01:05.000 --> 01:06.133
She's an actress.

01:06.167 --> 01:07.733
An actress.

01:07.767 --> 01:09.300
No kidding?

01:09.333 --> 01:10.533
[Rattle]

01:10.567 --> 01:14.100
**

01:14.133 --> 01:16.300
Does she have a voice?

01:16.333 --> 01:20.200
[Tape player powers on,
clicking]

01:20.233 --> 01:22.200
Charlie: And we don't want
our lives laid down

01:22.233 --> 01:26.133
by a multinational corporation
registered in Liechtenstein

01:26.167 --> 01:28.333
and banking
in the Dutch bloody Antilles.

01:28.367 --> 01:30.767
[Chuckles]
What's more is

01:30.800 --> 01:32.600
I, for one, don't think
the Jewish state

01:32.633 --> 01:34.667
has to be an imperialist
American garrison

01:34.700 --> 01:37.100
that treats Arabs like dung.

01:37.133 --> 01:38.867
Well, she's got a point.

01:38.900 --> 01:43.500
Hi, I'm Charmian.
Charmian Ross.

01:43.533 --> 01:47.267
We're thrilled to meet you,
Miss Ross, believe me.

01:47.300 --> 01:48.700
Please.

01:51.300 --> 01:53.300
Shall we begin,
Miss Ross?

01:53.333 --> 01:56.833
-Okay.
-Shall we...

01:56.867 --> 01:58.900
Becker: I'm studying
architecture now.

01:58.933 --> 02:00.100
[Grunts]

02:00.133 --> 02:03.233
No Israeli soldier
can doubt

02:03.267 --> 02:05.533
the great Gadi Becker's
right to live in peace,

02:05.567 --> 02:09.167
but...is this peace?

02:11.200 --> 02:14.167
This is about truth.

02:14.200 --> 02:16.667
They need
to believe her.

02:16.700 --> 02:20.267
I've heard you speak
their truth before.

02:20.300 --> 02:22.433
Believed it, even.

02:22.467 --> 02:25.267
That truth cost
an innocent girl's life.

02:27.267 --> 02:29.033
Innocent,
but not clever.

02:29.067 --> 02:33.267
Charlie here could learn
from you, Gadi.

02:33.300 --> 02:35.200
Surpass you, perhaps.

02:35.233 --> 02:37.233
I thought Charlie
was a boy's name.

02:41.533 --> 02:44.467
We will do it right
this time.

02:53.233 --> 02:55.000
[Cracks knuckles]

02:55.033 --> 02:56.233
[Grunts]

02:58.233 --> 02:59.833
[Clears throat]

03:04.333 --> 03:06.467
[Television turns off]

03:06.500 --> 03:11.300
[Tape player rattling]

03:11.333 --> 03:13.800
Khalil.

03:14.933 --> 03:16.967
Who knows?

03:17.000 --> 03:19.400
Maybe an imitator.

03:19.433 --> 03:20.600
[Tape player clicks]

03:20.633 --> 03:24.267
[Children shouting in distance]

03:27.867 --> 03:29.633
No killing.

03:31.700 --> 03:33.200
Autonomy.

03:34.400 --> 03:35.600
[Door opens]

03:41.633 --> 03:43.567
I left my hat.

03:45.167 --> 03:52.167
**

03:52.833 --> 03:59.833
**

04:00.567 --> 04:07.567
**

04:08.200 --> 04:15.200
**

04:15.867 --> 04:22.867
**

04:23.533 --> 04:30.533
**

04:31.200 --> 04:38.200
**

04:38.933 --> 04:45.900
**

04:46.633 --> 04:49.800
[Insects chirping]

04:49.833 --> 04:51.667
Who are you people?

04:51.700 --> 04:56.200
Who are we?
Come.

04:56.233 --> 04:57.900
Who are we?

04:57.933 --> 05:02.200
We are friends.

05:02.233 --> 05:06.667
Nonsectarian,
non-aligned friends

05:06.700 --> 05:10.867
deeply concerned, like you,
with the many wrong directions

05:10.900 --> 05:12.667
the world has taken.

05:12.700 --> 05:19.100
Yes, friends who must do the
unavoidable from time to time,

05:19.133 --> 05:21.167
but friends nonetheless.

05:24.167 --> 05:26.067
Beautiful, isn't it?

05:26.100 --> 05:28.400
Please come in.
[Claps hands]

05:30.300 --> 05:33.033
Yes, I'm sure you --
you must have

05:33.067 --> 05:34.900
a thousand questions
for us, Charlie.

05:34.933 --> 05:36.233
Of course
you do.

05:36.267 --> 05:38.033
You are
a curious mind.

05:38.067 --> 05:41.933
And we, too, also have
a thousands questions for you.

05:41.967 --> 05:44.900
**

05:44.933 --> 05:48.133
Make yourself comfortable.
Freshen up.

05:48.167 --> 05:52.667
And we shall go
through them all, okay?

05:52.700 --> 05:55.333
[Camera shutter clicks]

05:55.367 --> 05:58.200
Mm-hmm.

05:58.233 --> 06:00.000
[Camera shutter clicks,
metal rattling]

06:00.033 --> 06:07.000
**

06:07.033 --> 06:14.033
**

06:14.133 --> 06:15.700
It's an honor.

06:15.733 --> 06:18.433
I've heard a lot
about you.

06:18.467 --> 06:22.200
No, you haven't.

06:22.233 --> 06:24.367
The kids said
you made a fine couple

06:24.400 --> 06:27.167
up there on the Acropolis,
Gadi --

06:27.200 --> 06:31.367
like a pair
of movie stars.

06:31.400 --> 06:35.400
It was
a beautiful moment.

06:35.433 --> 06:37.867
[Water running]

06:41.800 --> 06:42.967
[Sniffs]

06:43.000 --> 06:44.233
[Water stops running]

06:46.033 --> 06:49.767
Sorry.
Protocol.

06:49.800 --> 06:51.800
[Clears throat]

06:51.833 --> 06:54.267
I need to go
for a number two.

06:58.300 --> 06:59.867
[Sighs]

06:59.900 --> 07:01.767
[Toilet lid slams]

07:02.867 --> 07:07.167
[Click, reels whirring]

07:07.200 --> 07:10.833
[Doors closing,
indistinct conversations
echoing in distance]

07:21.200 --> 07:24.433
[Lock clicks]

07:28.367 --> 07:30.200
[Door closes]

07:30.233 --> 07:33.867
[Doors closing,
indistinct conversations
echoing in distance]

07:48.267 --> 07:49.433
[Thud]

07:49.467 --> 07:51.133
[Briefcase hinges click]

08:02.133 --> 08:03.933
Charlie.

08:03.967 --> 08:06.867
You know what it cost me
to get you here?

08:06.900 --> 08:08.000
Your decency?

08:08.033 --> 08:09.733
Nothing so cheap.

08:09.767 --> 08:12.500
My career.
All for you.

08:15.100 --> 08:16.867
Didn't get what you needed
in London, then.

08:16.900 --> 08:20.500
Oh, I saw everything
I needed, Charlie.

08:20.533 --> 08:26.733
Everything to know that you
are worth this very moment.

08:26.767 --> 08:27.867
What did you say
your name was?

08:27.900 --> 08:29.100
I didn't.

08:29.133 --> 08:32.300
How about...Marty?

08:32.333 --> 08:34.533
Are you asking me
or telling me?

08:34.567 --> 08:36.700
And when God
finished making me,

08:36.733 --> 08:38.833
He had a few pieces of wire
left over,

08:38.867 --> 08:43.033
so He tied them up haphazardly
and put together Shimon.

08:43.067 --> 08:45.233
Say hello, Shimon.

08:45.267 --> 08:49.067
Mm.
Everyone else,
I think you know.

08:49.100 --> 08:50.733
[Footsteps approach]

08:53.333 --> 08:55.867
Ugh, you liar!

08:55.900 --> 08:57.233
I suggest you listen
to what they have --

08:57.267 --> 08:58.900
And I suggest
you go fuck yourself.

08:58.933 --> 09:00.100
Who are you?

09:00.133 --> 09:02.667
Do you have a problem
with Jews?

09:04.767 --> 09:07.833
Ethnically, culturally,
politically?

09:07.867 --> 09:09.233
We don't smell bad.

09:09.267 --> 09:11.500
Do you have
improper table manners?

09:11.533 --> 09:13.867
-No. Don't be stupid.
-Wonderful.

09:13.900 --> 09:15.600
Then I pray I can trust

09:15.633 --> 09:19.100
you won't jump out a window
or vomit

09:19.133 --> 09:22.433
if I say we are also
citizens of Israel.

09:22.467 --> 09:24.233
Do you have a bucket
just in case?

09:24.267 --> 09:26.233
[Scattered chuckles]

09:26.267 --> 09:30.833
Now, must all of us Jews
pack up our belongings,

09:30.867 --> 09:34.600
return to our former countries,
and begin again?

09:34.633 --> 09:36.433
Wait for
the next pogrom?

09:39.100 --> 09:41.033
[Sighs]

09:41.067 --> 09:43.433
I just want --

09:43.467 --> 09:46.233
Peace.

09:46.267 --> 09:49.433
Hmm?

09:49.467 --> 09:51.867
We're not here to attack
your politics, Charlie.

09:51.900 --> 09:55.400
In fact, we love
your crazy politics,

09:55.433 --> 10:02.100
every paradox and conflicted
spurt of anger or compassion.

10:02.133 --> 10:06.167
But we believe
in a bigger you --

10:06.200 --> 10:08.633
that you have talent
to waste,

10:08.667 --> 10:11.833
and you believe
it is being wasted.

10:11.867 --> 10:15.267
And if you decide to collaborate
with us on this performance,

10:15.300 --> 10:21.333
I swear to God, you will never
be wasted again.

10:21.367 --> 10:26.467
Put in its simplest form,
we are mounting a production.

10:26.500 --> 10:27.833
Hmm?

10:27.867 --> 10:32.133
Now, there will be no cut,
no curtain,

10:32.167 --> 10:34.233
constant improvisation.

10:36.967 --> 10:39.533
[Chuckling]
Well, shit.

10:39.567 --> 10:42.333
I've been kidnapped by an
experimental theater company.

10:42.367 --> 10:44.000
[Laughter]

10:44.033 --> 10:46.433
Experimental certainly.

10:46.467 --> 10:49.533
Your audience, they won't even
know they are watching.

10:49.567 --> 10:51.233
But they will be
grateful --

10:51.267 --> 10:53.700
kids, their parents,

10:53.733 --> 10:55.567
innocent bystanders

10:55.600 --> 10:59.000
who'd get a piece of shrapnel
in their throat

10:59.033 --> 11:02.100
when a bomb goes off
right beside them

11:02.133 --> 11:03.733
were it not for you.

11:05.733 --> 11:08.333
Should you want to go home,
of course,

11:08.367 --> 11:14.100
back to your, uh --
uh, pub theaters,

11:14.133 --> 11:16.333
your lonely brilliance,

11:16.367 --> 11:18.300
no one is stopping you.

11:18.333 --> 11:23.533
But if you are at all
intrigued by this role,

11:23.567 --> 11:30.533
we need to ask you a final round
of questions...tonight.

11:34.933 --> 11:38.133
What's the character?

11:38.167 --> 11:39.333
A terrorist.

11:39.367 --> 11:41.133
[Exhales deeply]

11:41.167 --> 11:46.733
**

11:46.767 --> 11:49.300
[Lock rattles, disengages]

11:49.333 --> 11:51.100
[Chain jingles]

11:51.133 --> 11:54.067
**

11:54.100 --> 11:55.733
No!

11:55.767 --> 11:58.533
**

11:58.567 --> 12:00.167
Go back.

12:00.200 --> 12:03.833
**

12:03.867 --> 12:08.033
[Doors closing,
echoing in distance]

12:08.067 --> 12:10.300
Are you okay?

12:10.333 --> 12:12.833
I'm here
to talk to you.

12:12.867 --> 12:14.667
I'll be fine.

12:19.933 --> 12:24.067
[Door closes, lock clicks]

12:24.100 --> 12:26.133
Dear God, Salim,
I'm so sorry.

12:29.100 --> 12:30.600
My name is Joanna.

12:30.633 --> 12:33.800
I'm an observer for
the International Aid Alliance,

12:33.833 --> 12:37.300
and it is our job to --
Where am I?

12:37.333 --> 12:39.067
I'm not allowed to say.

12:43.067 --> 12:45.333
Am I still in Greece?

12:45.367 --> 12:47.600
Have they mistreated you at all
since your arrival?

12:47.633 --> 12:49.833
[Chain jingles]

12:49.867 --> 12:51.600
Are you getting enough fruit
and vegetables?

12:51.633 --> 12:52.600
[Chuckles]

12:52.633 --> 12:56.267
[Door opens]
[Whistling]

13:01.267 --> 13:04.233
What is he, a puppy?

13:04.267 --> 13:07.767
We don't have time.

13:07.800 --> 13:09.500
This side is clean, yes?

13:11.733 --> 13:14.367
We've got to get
that drop-off location.

13:14.400 --> 13:17.167
[Door opens]

13:17.200 --> 13:18.933
Look what I have.

13:21.400 --> 13:23.367
[Door closes, lock clicks]

13:23.400 --> 13:25.867
Charlie:
Fire away, then, Mart.

13:25.900 --> 13:27.300
Ask me anything.

13:33.300 --> 13:34.567
[Tape recorder clicks]

13:34.600 --> 13:36.233
Kurtz: Let's begin
with your family.

13:36.267 --> 13:37.100
[Pen clicks]

13:43.800 --> 13:48.133
Israeli oranges
are the best in the world.

13:48.167 --> 13:52.067
[Chewing]

13:52.100 --> 13:55.533
Israeli?

13:55.567 --> 13:57.167
[Chuckles]
Mm.

13:57.200 --> 14:01.367
It's the only good thing
they have...

14:01.400 --> 14:06.733
because they were grown
on Palestinian soil.

14:06.767 --> 14:08.567
[Chewing]

14:08.600 --> 14:10.233
If you want to get out
of solitary,

14:10.267 --> 14:14.433
you have to pacify your enemies
without betraying your friends.

14:14.467 --> 14:16.500
I have no friends.

14:16.533 --> 14:18.300
No one does.

14:18.333 --> 14:19.900
Not at first.

14:19.933 --> 14:21.667
But they will find out.

14:24.200 --> 14:27.567
Do you have family
you can write to?

14:27.600 --> 14:30.900
I will only write
to my lawyers.

14:30.933 --> 14:34.100
Of course, but family
plays better with the press.

14:34.133 --> 14:39.167
[Exhaling sharply]

14:41.533 --> 14:42.600
What about your mother?

14:42.633 --> 14:44.467
Jane Ashcroft.

14:44.500 --> 14:46.000
-Dead?
-Drunk.

14:46.033 --> 14:48.333
Because of your father.

14:48.367 --> 14:50.467
Because my father
was a criminal, yes.

14:50.500 --> 14:53.300
Did the school ask you to leave
because of these problems?

14:53.333 --> 14:54.700
Yeah.

14:54.733 --> 14:56.100
It was heartless,
but we didn't have money

14:56.133 --> 14:57.467
to pay
the school fees.

14:57.500 --> 14:59.133
So, after that
fall from grace --

14:59.167 --> 15:01.000
He went to prison,
and we lost everything.

15:01.033 --> 15:02.333
Mm.

15:02.367 --> 15:04.100
I've been fending for myself
since I was 15,

15:04.133 --> 15:06.767
but it was the best thing
that ever happened to me.

15:06.800 --> 15:08.067
Hmm.

15:08.100 --> 15:09.467
So, as soon as you could,
you rebelled

15:09.500 --> 15:11.967
to the stage
and radical politics.

15:12.000 --> 15:15.067
Oh, there are other ways of
rebelling than radical politics.

15:15.100 --> 15:16.367
Such as?

15:16.400 --> 15:19.033
-Sex, of course.
-Hmm.

15:19.067 --> 15:21.967
The essential basis
to any revolt.

15:22.000 --> 15:26.733
We are not interested
in all those failures, Charlie.

15:26.767 --> 15:29.967
Was it your father
who made you feel so angry?

15:34.900 --> 15:36.633
Can we take a break?
In a moment.

15:36.667 --> 15:40.033
It must have upset you,
his going to prison like that,

15:40.067 --> 15:41.633
conning people
out of their money.

15:41.667 --> 15:44.633
It was humiliation.

15:44.667 --> 15:46.667
The bailiffs coming in,
ransacking the place,

15:46.700 --> 15:49.700
Mum having to apply for benefits
just to put food on the table.

15:49.733 --> 15:52.633
That sort of thing didn't
happen to people like us.

15:55.700 --> 15:59.033
Kurtz:
So, what did happen?

15:59.067 --> 16:01.633
They took it all.

16:01.667 --> 16:04.400
Everything.

16:04.433 --> 16:07.233
My childhood,
our home...

16:07.267 --> 16:08.233
Hmm.

16:08.267 --> 16:09.600
...our happiness.

16:09.633 --> 16:13.800
And where were you
when your father died?

16:13.833 --> 16:17.900
Standing
in a bus shelter...

16:17.933 --> 16:22.500
outside the prison,
waiting for the gates to open.

16:22.533 --> 16:24.033
Standing
in the pissing rain.

16:24.067 --> 16:25.267
The date?

16:25.300 --> 16:27.967
15th of July, 1975.

16:28.000 --> 16:30.400
Rain in July?

16:30.433 --> 16:32.600
You've never been to England,
I take it.

16:32.633 --> 16:37.400
Was your mother there with you,
Charlie, when he died?

16:37.433 --> 16:39.800
**

16:39.833 --> 16:43.600
[Crying]

16:43.633 --> 16:49.300
**

16:51.600 --> 16:54.400
[Claps hands]
Let's take that break now.

16:56.000 --> 16:59.633
[Michel singing
Palestinian folk song]

17:07.300 --> 17:09.267
[Door opens]

17:09.300 --> 17:14.767
[Singing continues]

17:21.967 --> 17:25.333
[Song trailing off]

17:25.367 --> 17:26.533
[Light clicks]

17:26.567 --> 17:28.133
[Lighter clicks]

17:28.167 --> 17:30.600
**

17:30.633 --> 17:31.800
[Lighter clicks]

17:31.833 --> 17:38.733
**

17:38.767 --> 17:45.700
**

17:45.733 --> 17:52.600
**

17:52.633 --> 17:55.200
[Lighter clicks]

17:55.233 --> 18:01.533
**

18:01.567 --> 18:07.867
**

18:07.900 --> 18:10.867
Who gives her
the home truth?

18:10.900 --> 18:12.500
It should come from me.

18:12.533 --> 18:18.100
**

18:18.133 --> 18:19.867
Thank you, Gadi.

18:19.900 --> 18:24.367
Miss Bach: [Echoing]
Here you go, like you asked.

18:24.400 --> 18:27.100
You'll have to write
in English.

18:27.133 --> 18:30.900
Otherwise, they won't let
your sister read it.

18:30.933 --> 18:33.967
These people
don't allow Arabic.

18:34.000 --> 18:35.900
My lawyers?

18:35.933 --> 18:39.700
They responded already, dear.
Last week.

18:39.733 --> 18:41.100
Last week?

18:41.133 --> 18:43.867
Your lawyers told you
to write to Fatmeh.

18:43.900 --> 18:46.833
I-I don't remember.
Really?

18:46.867 --> 18:51.033
You don't remember me giving you
an orange last week, either?

18:51.067 --> 18:52.467
I remember that.

18:52.500 --> 18:54.367
That's good.

18:54.400 --> 18:55.833
But I'm telling you,

18:55.867 --> 18:58.667
your lawyers told you
to write to Fatmeh.

18:58.700 --> 19:00.533
That's your sister's name,
isn't it?

19:00.567 --> 19:02.133
Fatmeh.

19:02.167 --> 19:06.867
You'll have to tell her
you're missing, at least.

19:06.900 --> 19:09.433
Sh-She...

19:09.467 --> 19:11.867
She already knows

19:11.900 --> 19:18.867
if -- if I have been here
a week.

19:19.433 --> 19:21.000
Oh?

19:21.033 --> 19:23.133
I...

19:23.167 --> 19:28.567
I call in
every three days.

19:29.467 --> 19:31.000
[Door closes, lock clicks]

19:31.033 --> 19:32.633
Daniel:
Contact every three days.

19:32.667 --> 19:34.233
But never
the same way twice.

19:34.267 --> 19:35.467
We need to tell Marty.

19:35.500 --> 19:37.267
[Birds chirping]

19:37.300 --> 19:39.000
Kurtz:
Now, I'm afraid we found

19:39.033 --> 19:41.067
some rather worrying
contradictions

19:41.100 --> 19:43.833
in what you told us,
Charlie.

19:43.867 --> 19:45.767
Charlie: I thought
we weren't talking politics.

19:45.800 --> 19:48.567
We're not.
We're talking beliefs.

19:48.600 --> 19:52.967
The reasoning behind every one
of your political choices --

19:53.000 --> 19:54.400
Look, I don't want
the world wiped out

19:54.433 --> 19:56.100
in some
dick-swinging contest

19:56.133 --> 19:57.500
between some
fascist demagogues

19:57.533 --> 19:59.433
we've never heard of --
Yes, yes, yes, yes.

19:59.467 --> 20:02.967
We've -- We've heard all
your rehearsed quotations.

20:03.000 --> 20:04.600
Oh, piss off.

20:06.100 --> 20:09.167
You say you're the radical soul
here, Charlie.

20:09.200 --> 20:11.600
But when are
you going to go out

20:11.633 --> 20:15.833
and do something
about all this talk?

20:15.867 --> 20:19.800
Have you not the courage
to steal,

20:19.833 --> 20:22.133
to kill for
these hearts and minds

20:22.167 --> 20:24.533
enslaved by
your capitalist overlords?

20:24.567 --> 20:26.233
Is that what you want --
stealing and killing?

20:26.267 --> 20:28.533
I want to know you stand
by your promise.

20:28.567 --> 20:29.867
Then stop
twisting my words.

20:29.900 --> 20:31.333
Are you recanting
your stated position?

20:31.367 --> 20:32.867
I don't have
a stated position!

20:32.900 --> 20:35.400
Oh. No commitment
to activism,

20:35.433 --> 20:36.733
except that
you are unaligned.

20:36.767 --> 20:39.933
-Yes!
-Peacefully unaligned, too.

20:39.967 --> 20:42.000
You belong
to the extreme center.

20:42.033 --> 20:45.733
Just like you're
a peace-loving Israeli.

20:45.767 --> 20:47.400
[Laughs sarcastically]

20:49.567 --> 20:52.133
Hmm.

20:55.133 --> 20:58.500
-That was nothing.
-Yes.

20:58.533 --> 21:01.100
Quite
an illegal nothing

21:01.133 --> 21:03.500
for someone
who is anti-violence.

21:03.533 --> 21:05.633
Weapons training.
With dummy guns, look!

21:05.667 --> 21:08.733
Sabotage techniques.
Combat skills.

21:08.767 --> 21:10.733
It was Al's scene.
I didn't really get --

21:10.767 --> 21:12.967
I thought it was just
some cheap weekend away.

21:13.000 --> 21:14.500
You can get 10 years
for this.

21:14.533 --> 21:17.200
What?!
No, it wasn't like that!

21:17.233 --> 21:19.200
I was playing.
I go with the flow.

21:19.233 --> 21:21.900
I take whatever role
that is on offer, okay?

21:21.933 --> 21:24.300
Playing.

21:25.833 --> 21:31.167
Now, do you remember
the last session,

21:31.200 --> 21:36.667
devoted to the lamentable
expansion of Zionism?

21:36.700 --> 21:41.467
The leading performer was
a Palestinian revolutionary.

21:41.500 --> 21:43.533
Do you not recall
this speaker?

21:43.567 --> 21:48.100
I -- I mean --
"The gun is my passport
to my homeland.

21:48.133 --> 21:51.300
We are no longer refugees.
We are revolutionary people."

21:51.333 --> 21:53.667
All right, I'm superficial.
I get it.

21:53.700 --> 21:56.267
But I didn't
do anything.

21:56.300 --> 21:57.600
Didn't do anything?

22:00.867 --> 22:03.067
No more lies, Charlie.

22:07.067 --> 22:10.633
You say you went to this forum
a couple of times.

22:10.667 --> 22:12.467
That correct?
-It was a couple of times.

22:12.500 --> 22:15.500
Couple is two.
Oh, my God.

22:15.533 --> 22:17.467
Two or three.
What the hell?

22:17.500 --> 22:20.067
I went to visit my aunt
in the country

22:20.100 --> 22:21.700
a couple of times
last year.

22:21.733 --> 22:23.900
That could be three.
Four is possible.

22:23.933 --> 22:25.100
Five, I guess.
Five.

22:25.133 --> 22:26.833
Oh, with five,
it's half a dozen.

22:26.867 --> 22:30.133
You want to revise
"couple," Charlie?

22:30.167 --> 22:33.267
I said "a couple."
I mean a couple.

22:33.300 --> 22:35.100
And what do we
make it out to be?

22:35.133 --> 22:37.600
Six times,
all documented.

22:37.633 --> 22:39.500
Well, where does
she get two from?

22:39.533 --> 22:40.900
She's lying.

22:40.933 --> 22:43.333
[Chuckles sarcastically]

22:43.367 --> 22:45.533
Charlie deceived us.

22:45.567 --> 22:46.833
That's
so disappointing.

22:46.867 --> 22:50.000
-That sure is.
-It's a phrase.

22:50.033 --> 22:52.300
I -- I was just acting.

22:52.333 --> 22:54.500
-Like you've been acting here.
-Yes!

22:54.533 --> 22:56.800
All your politics,
all your claims.
Yes.

22:56.833 --> 22:58.633
Like you've acted
every day

22:58.667 --> 23:02.500
since the great fall
of your criminal father!
Yes. Oh, my God!

23:02.533 --> 23:06.867
Joseph, please tell me
why any of this matters.

23:09.467 --> 23:13.167
We know your father never
went to prison, Charlie.

23:13.200 --> 23:15.300
**

23:15.333 --> 23:17.700
You never had
the bailiffs in.

23:17.733 --> 23:20.900
There was no rain
on the 15th of July.

23:20.933 --> 23:23.200
You were expelled
from St. Floras

23:23.233 --> 23:26.200
after you were caught
sleeping with a local boy.

23:26.233 --> 23:33.000
Your parents forgave you,
as they always did everything.

23:33.033 --> 23:36.467
Then, one day, your father died
of a stroke in his home.

23:36.500 --> 23:38.933
**

23:38.967 --> 23:41.933
And you were heartbroken...

23:41.967 --> 23:47.567
because, in fact, you adored
your bourgeois father.

23:47.600 --> 23:50.267
We understand how you've spun
a more dramatic fiction

23:50.300 --> 23:52.333
for your life,

23:52.367 --> 23:55.400
one that plays in interviews
and auditions,

23:55.433 --> 23:58.933
at political forums
with your so-called friends --

23:58.967 --> 24:03.367
one that
feels more like you

24:03.400 --> 24:07.333
than the ordinary
suburban reality.

24:07.367 --> 24:10.600
**

24:10.633 --> 24:14.800
And we love you for it,
because we are just the same.

24:14.833 --> 24:20.900
**

24:20.933 --> 24:26.967
**

24:27.000 --> 24:28.167
[Screams]

24:28.200 --> 24:30.367
[Whimpers]
Let me go!

24:30.400 --> 24:32.000
Hey, hey, hey.

24:32.033 --> 24:35.967
[Sobbing]

24:39.033 --> 24:42.000
Kurtz:
Did great, kid.

24:42.033 --> 24:43.300
You just
got the part.

24:43.333 --> 24:46.900
[Breathing shakily]

24:48.100 --> 24:49.900
[Equipment rattles]

24:55.833 --> 24:57.400
[Doors slide open]

24:57.433 --> 25:01.433
[Moaning]

25:05.933 --> 25:07.467
Every three days?

25:07.500 --> 25:08.700
Litvak:
That's what she said.

25:08.733 --> 25:11.467
His last contact
was two days ago.

25:11.500 --> 25:13.300
We need to march
double time.

25:13.333 --> 25:16.967
[Teleprinter clacking]

25:24.900 --> 25:26.467
Message from
Noah Gavron.

25:26.500 --> 25:28.133
Mm-hmm.

25:28.167 --> 25:30.067
"On no account
will you admit to her

25:30.100 --> 25:32.233
that you are
Israeli subjects.

25:32.267 --> 25:34.800
Insist that you pose
as Americans."

25:36.667 --> 25:39.233
[Both laugh]

25:39.267 --> 25:41.333
I love it.

25:41.367 --> 25:45.133
Cable back, "Yes.
Repeat, no."

25:45.167 --> 25:47.467
[Both chuckle]

25:47.500 --> 25:50.833
[Kurtz whistling]

25:54.767 --> 25:56.533
He's happy
since you came back.

25:58.633 --> 26:00.367
It's not good
for him.

26:14.300 --> 26:15.667
[Grunts]

26:17.433 --> 26:20.033
He's lost his stomach,
I can tell.

26:20.067 --> 26:23.867
When the moment comes,
Gadi will do what is necessary.

26:29.267 --> 26:31.867
You haven't told him
about the Mercedes?

26:31.900 --> 26:36.633
**

26:36.667 --> 26:39.967
Timing is everything,
Shimon.

26:40.000 --> 26:41.200
Hmm?

26:41.233 --> 26:47.767
**

26:47.800 --> 26:50.767
I wonder how the weather is
in Munich.

26:50.800 --> 26:53.567
[Tape player clicks]

26:53.600 --> 26:56.600
Michel: We fled their tanks
on the West Bank...

26:56.633 --> 26:59.933
Becker: We fled their tanks
on the West Bank across Jordan.

26:59.967 --> 27:01.533
Michel: I asked my mother
what was happening...

27:01.567 --> 27:02.933
I asked my mother
what was happening...

27:02.967 --> 27:04.633
...and she said to me...
...and she said to me...

27:04.667 --> 27:06.333
...to me, the youngest...
...to me, the youngest...

27:06.367 --> 27:07.733
..."What the Westerners
did to the Jews..."

27:07.767 --> 27:09.333
..."What the Westerners
did to the Jews..."

27:09.367 --> 27:10.733
"...the Zionists
now do to us."

27:10.767 --> 27:11.967
"...the Zionists
now do to us."

27:12.000 --> 27:12.933
I'm finished.

27:12.967 --> 27:15.133
When I was 8...
When I was 8...

27:15.167 --> 27:16.333
...I was driven
from our land.
[Door closes]

27:16.367 --> 27:17.433
...I was driven
from our land.

27:17.467 --> 27:20.133
The Gun
and the Return...

27:20.167 --> 27:23.567
[Exhales deeply]
The Gun
and the Return,

27:23.600 --> 27:25.467
they are one for us.

27:27.367 --> 27:29.433
[Tape player clicks]

27:29.467 --> 27:31.067
[Groans]

27:34.033 --> 27:36.567
How's the lip?

27:36.600 --> 27:39.000
Well, I'll never play
the trumpet again.

27:39.033 --> 27:40.333
[Chuckles]

27:42.467 --> 27:44.733
[Sighs]

27:47.600 --> 27:48.900
If I'm going
to do this,

27:48.933 --> 27:52.333
I have to know what it is
I'm deciding to do.

27:52.367 --> 27:56.800
And in order to know,
you first have to decide.

27:56.833 --> 27:59.100
Well, that's
just marvelous.

27:59.133 --> 28:03.167
[Birds chirping in distance]

28:03.200 --> 28:05.000
This job,
is it dangerous?

28:05.033 --> 28:06.633
Incredibly.

28:10.933 --> 28:13.100
This is the secret world,
Charlie.

28:17.100 --> 28:18.833
Are you in or out?

28:24.500 --> 28:25.667
Who am I?

28:25.700 --> 28:28.567
You.

28:28.600 --> 28:31.333
And who are you?

28:31.367 --> 28:34.267
You know me as Michel.

28:34.300 --> 28:40.233
**

28:40.267 --> 28:42.700
And...

28:42.733 --> 28:44.367
are we in love?

28:44.400 --> 28:46.133
Infatuated.

28:46.167 --> 28:49.633
**

28:49.667 --> 28:51.633
Promise me
something.

28:51.667 --> 28:54.467
If I go along with this,
I want complete honesty.

28:54.500 --> 28:57.867
So,
for everything I do,

28:57.900 --> 29:02.333
you answer a question
for me in return.

29:02.367 --> 29:05.133
So we're even.

29:05.167 --> 29:06.333
Okay?

29:06.367 --> 29:12.067
**

29:12.100 --> 29:14.600
Wear this today.

29:14.633 --> 29:16.833
Your hair up.

29:16.867 --> 29:18.800
There's underwear
in the bathroom.

29:18.833 --> 29:24.200
**

29:24.233 --> 29:27.400
Michel likes it
when you wear bold colors.

29:27.433 --> 29:31.700
[Exhales] Hmm.

29:31.733 --> 29:34.033
That's from our lovemaking
last night.

29:34.067 --> 29:36.600
How memorable.

29:36.633 --> 29:42.433
**

29:42.467 --> 29:48.233
**

29:48.267 --> 29:51.567
If the Israelis bomb our
villages with fighter jets...

29:51.600 --> 29:55.167
[Michel speaking indistinctly
through headphones]

29:55.200 --> 29:57.167
**

29:57.200 --> 29:58.367
[Tape player clicks]

29:58.400 --> 30:02.633
**

30:02.667 --> 30:04.367
Very good.

30:04.400 --> 30:09.633
**

30:09.667 --> 30:11.800
Rachel: They're still working
on a drop-off location,

30:11.833 --> 30:13.567
but we need to make a stop.

30:13.600 --> 30:20.567
**

30:23.100 --> 30:27.167
Becker: From now on, everything
I say and do is crucial.

30:27.200 --> 30:29.167
We're building
a fiction,

30:29.200 --> 30:31.433
and our audience is everywhere
all the time.

30:45.467 --> 30:49.000
Our love affair
has been secret.

30:49.033 --> 30:50.433
Last night
was our first together

30:50.467 --> 30:53.033
after weeks
of waiting.

30:53.067 --> 30:54.233
The whole time
you were in Greece,

30:54.267 --> 30:56.367
you were aching
to join me.

30:56.400 --> 31:00.133
That's why you gave Alistair
and the others the slip.

31:00.167 --> 31:03.000
And what about
Joseph?

31:03.033 --> 31:05.500
The creepy businessman
who tried to chat you up?

31:05.533 --> 31:06.533
Mm-hmm.

31:06.567 --> 31:09.900
[Scoffs]
He was nothing.

31:09.933 --> 31:12.533
The moment you got
in this car in Athens,

31:12.567 --> 31:16.100
you were with me --
Michel.

31:16.133 --> 31:17.333
Ah.

31:17.367 --> 31:19.700
I took you to the Acropolis
at night

31:19.733 --> 31:21.567
to celebrate
our reunion.

31:21.600 --> 31:26.667
**

31:26.700 --> 31:30.300
We kissed
in the ruins.

31:30.333 --> 31:31.700
I'm romantic
that way.

31:31.733 --> 31:34.367
[Chuckles] Hmm.
Gestural.

31:34.400 --> 31:37.467
Not terribly into that,
I'm afraid.

31:37.500 --> 31:39.200
You've never felt
like this before.

31:39.233 --> 31:41.867
[Chuckles]
Have I not?

31:41.900 --> 31:43.067
Okay.

31:43.100 --> 31:45.067
No.
Oh.

31:45.100 --> 31:47.100
I disapprove
of women smoking.

31:47.133 --> 31:50.733
And I disapprove of
men who disapprove of
women smoking, mush.

31:50.767 --> 31:53.267
It -- It is your pleasure to
obey me in these small matters.

31:53.300 --> 31:56.300
Jose, love --
Michel!

31:56.333 --> 32:01.033
Mickey, love, I don't really see
how this is gonna work.

32:01.067 --> 32:02.967
I mean, I'm still meant
to be myself

32:03.000 --> 32:05.067
or a credible version,
right?

32:05.100 --> 32:06.433
Exactly credible.

32:06.467 --> 32:07.833
Hmm.
Well, then.

32:07.867 --> 32:09.067
[Lighter clicks]

32:11.600 --> 32:13.433
[Inhales]

32:13.467 --> 32:14.900
[Exhales]

32:14.933 --> 32:16.767
[Window cranks down]

32:18.933 --> 32:22.533
Chauvinist, then,
this Michel?

32:22.567 --> 32:25.333
[Exhales]

32:25.367 --> 32:28.433
Or some sort of
wicked stereotype

32:28.467 --> 32:30.167
you lot
have cooked up?

32:32.700 --> 32:34.600
Well he is,
isn't he?

32:34.633 --> 32:38.400
There is nothing stereotypical
about me, Charlie.

32:38.433 --> 32:42.100
One day you'll meet my sister,
Fatmeh, our inspiration,

32:42.133 --> 32:43.833
and then
you will understand.

32:43.867 --> 32:45.633
Our Palestinian women
have a dignity

32:45.667 --> 32:47.833
you can't even
begin to imagine.

32:47.867 --> 32:52.300
Ah. Palestinian.

32:52.333 --> 32:55.233
[Exhales] I see.

32:55.267 --> 32:57.033
Tricky.

33:01.233 --> 33:02.400
[Schwilli blows]

33:02.433 --> 33:04.367
I've checked
the law firm.

33:04.400 --> 33:05.967
Zurich, legitimate.

33:06.000 --> 33:08.500
Schwilli:
Just as well.

33:08.533 --> 33:11.200
How close are you
on Fatmeh's reply?

33:11.233 --> 33:13.600
Just an envelope
to go.

33:13.633 --> 33:16.167
I hope I got
Fatmeh's tone right.

33:16.200 --> 33:19.367
We need to know
where he was taking that car.

33:19.400 --> 33:23.400
[Birds chirping]

33:23.433 --> 33:25.167
Miss Bach:
"No words can tell how much

33:25.200 --> 33:28.167
I admire the sacrifice
you are making.

33:28.200 --> 33:33.833
But we must leave you now
for the good of our cause.

33:33.867 --> 33:38.833
No one will forget your name
or the pride we all feel in you.

33:38.867 --> 33:41.800
Fatmeh and Miss Bach: You will
become a blessed martyr,

33:41.833 --> 33:45.633
like your brothers
Fawaz and Abed.

33:45.667 --> 33:48.933
Fatmeh:
This I swear as your sister.

33:48.967 --> 33:53.767
And so, I pray that
you are given courage

33:53.800 --> 33:57.433
when your time comes.

33:57.467 --> 33:59.033
Your Fatmeh."

33:59.067 --> 34:01.933
[Paper rustles]

34:01.967 --> 34:04.767
**

34:04.800 --> 34:07.000
Salim?

34:07.033 --> 34:09.033
Is Fatmeh going
to help you?

34:09.067 --> 34:10.633
**

34:10.667 --> 34:14.967
I've tried everything,
but it's beyond me now.

34:15.000 --> 34:17.000
They're sending an expert
to talk to you.

34:17.033 --> 34:18.600
[Door opens]

34:18.633 --> 34:20.100
[Voices echoing in distance]

34:20.133 --> 34:21.400
All right.

34:21.433 --> 34:22.933
It's time.

34:22.967 --> 34:26.033
-I'm sorry.
-Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

34:26.067 --> 34:27.400
Let go.
Let go.

34:31.967 --> 34:33.300
It's good
that you're eating.

34:33.333 --> 34:36.000
You'll need
your strength.

34:36.033 --> 34:39.900
[Screams]

34:39.933 --> 34:43.133
[Screaming, thud]

34:43.167 --> 34:45.133
Very good.

34:45.167 --> 34:47.733
[Volume lowers]
What did you say?

34:47.767 --> 34:50.467
I said you did a very good job
in there, Miss Bach.

34:50.500 --> 34:53.500
Thank you.
This is also
equally impressive.

34:53.533 --> 34:55.867
Tell me the details.

34:55.900 --> 34:59.267
So...

34:59.300 --> 35:03.367
that's Charlie's timeline,
and here's Michel's.

35:03.400 --> 35:04.367
Hmm.

35:04.400 --> 35:05.667
We've tracked
his movements

35:05.700 --> 35:08.533
using his receipts
and matchbooks.

35:08.567 --> 35:11.933
They coincide
in London and Greece.

35:11.967 --> 35:13.267
And while they're apart,

35:13.300 --> 35:15.500
he writes to her
to keep up the romance.

35:15.533 --> 35:18.033
Miss Bach created
some moving love ballads for me.

35:18.067 --> 35:20.433
Oh, yes.
[Sighs]

35:20.467 --> 35:22.567
We need to put all this back
in the apartment, Marty.

35:22.600 --> 35:23.933
They'll come
looking soon.

35:23.967 --> 35:25.633
[Slurps ice pop]

35:25.667 --> 35:29.833
How are we
on the car's destination?

35:29.867 --> 35:31.667
Without that, we are
on the diving board,

35:31.700 --> 35:34.100
and the pool is empty.

35:34.133 --> 35:37.467
He's on the edge,
I think.

35:37.500 --> 35:39.300
-Hmm.
-You gonna get it out of him?

35:39.333 --> 35:41.100
[Michel screaming continues]

35:41.133 --> 35:42.433
No.

35:42.467 --> 35:45.867
Keep me in reserve,
just in case.

35:48.300 --> 35:50.800
So, who will be
the expert?

35:50.833 --> 35:55.000
[Slurps ice pop]

35:55.033 --> 35:57.400
[Greek folk music playing]

35:57.433 --> 36:00.200
[Indistinct conversations]

36:00.233 --> 36:03.000
-Hmm.
-Thank you.

36:03.033 --> 36:05.400
[Folk music continues]

36:05.433 --> 36:07.033
When did I meet you...

36:07.067 --> 36:08.400
Michel?

36:08.433 --> 36:11.267
Although it was long
before I was born,

36:11.300 --> 36:13.500
I tell you often
about Al Nakba.

36:13.533 --> 36:15.033
Al Nakba?

36:15.067 --> 36:19.000
The Catastrophe
of 1948.

36:19.033 --> 36:23.067
The Israelis call it
the War of Independence.

36:23.100 --> 36:24.633
It's when your
British betrayed us,

36:24.667 --> 36:26.367
and the Zionists drove us
from our homeland.

36:26.400 --> 36:28.433
No, I'm not talking about
your great-great-grandad.

36:28.467 --> 36:30.367
I'm talking about
you and me.

36:30.400 --> 36:33.900
For 20 years, my father
had faith in the Zionists

36:33.933 --> 36:36.200
to see reason.

36:36.233 --> 36:40.033
And then came
the massacres of '67.

36:40.067 --> 36:42.433
They shot him,

36:42.467 --> 36:46.767
made me stand next to him
as they did.

36:46.800 --> 36:49.967
We fled their tanks from
the West Bank across Jordan.

36:50.000 --> 36:51.800
And I asked my mother
what was happening,

36:51.833 --> 36:54.400
and she said to me --
to me, the youngest...

36:54.433 --> 36:57.200
Oh, God.
You're him.

36:57.233 --> 37:00.033
..."What the Westerners
did to the Jews,

37:00.067 --> 37:01.033
the Zionists...

37:01.067 --> 37:02.733
Now do to us."

37:02.767 --> 37:06.167
**

37:06.200 --> 37:10.667
When I was 8,
I was driven from our land.

37:10.700 --> 37:14.667
When I was 10, I joined
the Ashbal with my brothers.

37:14.700 --> 37:17.367
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

37:17.400 --> 37:20.133
What's -- What's an Ashbal?
Sorry.

37:20.167 --> 37:23.200
**

37:23.233 --> 37:24.833
A children's militia.

37:24.867 --> 37:26.733
If children can be born,
they can also...

37:26.767 --> 37:27.933
Fight.

37:27.967 --> 37:30.500
**

37:30.533 --> 37:35.400
When I was 11, I crouched
in a homemade shelter

37:35.433 --> 37:39.100
while the Jordanians
poured rockets into our camp.

37:39.133 --> 37:42.733
**

37:42.767 --> 37:46.133
The Gun
and the Return...

37:46.167 --> 37:48.733
They are one
for us.

37:48.767 --> 37:50.967
That's why
you chose me, then.

37:51.000 --> 37:52.333
Because I was
at that forum?

37:52.367 --> 37:55.000
I fell in love with you
instantly.

37:55.033 --> 37:58.733
[Greek folk music playing]

37:58.767 --> 38:00.967
His eyes, they...

38:01.000 --> 38:03.367
they were --
Endless.

38:03.400 --> 38:10.400
**

38:11.733 --> 38:15.400
You look nothing
like him.

38:15.433 --> 38:17.133
It's not just
what they see.

38:17.167 --> 38:18.467
It's what
you believe.

38:18.500 --> 38:20.500
Where is he now?

38:20.533 --> 38:22.667
Here, with you.

38:22.700 --> 38:29.700
**

38:29.933 --> 38:31.300
Is this what
you're after, then?

38:31.333 --> 38:34.667
**

38:34.700 --> 38:36.900
It's perfect.

38:36.933 --> 38:40.500
Don't confuse drama
with reality, Jose.

38:40.533 --> 38:42.033
That's very dangerous.

38:42.067 --> 38:45.033
**

38:45.067 --> 38:47.467
I'll remember that...

38:47.500 --> 38:50.100
coming from
a professional.

38:50.133 --> 38:53.033
Ironic,
don't you think?

38:53.067 --> 38:55.900
The first time we met, it was me
onstage and you in the audience.

38:55.933 --> 38:57.133
You watched the matinee

38:57.167 --> 38:58.833
and stayed for
the evening performance,

38:58.867 --> 39:00.433
and everyone saw you.

39:00.467 --> 39:02.233
It was the longest day
of my life.

39:02.267 --> 39:03.633
[Laughs]

39:03.667 --> 39:07.433
But you were excellent,
though.

39:07.467 --> 39:09.900
Far better than
the theater deserved.
No, no.

39:09.933 --> 39:11.600
Too late, love.

39:11.633 --> 39:14.700
[Folk music continues]

39:14.733 --> 39:16.000
[Snaps fingers]

39:16.033 --> 39:17.200
[Scoffs]

39:17.233 --> 39:18.800
**

39:18.833 --> 39:20.633
Sorry.

39:20.667 --> 39:23.333
[Chair creaks]

39:23.367 --> 39:26.200
**

39:26.233 --> 39:27.400
-Keep the tip.
-Right.

39:27.433 --> 39:29.333
Efharisto.

39:29.367 --> 39:34.500
**

39:34.533 --> 39:39.800
**

39:39.833 --> 39:44.300
Anna Witgen -- the Swedish trash
who delivered the bomb,

39:44.333 --> 39:48.300
the one who killed the boy,
Gabriel.

39:48.333 --> 39:49.900
Where did
you send her?

39:49.933 --> 39:53.200
[Footsteps, doors closing
echoing in distance]

39:53.233 --> 39:56.700
Does your big brother Khalil
let you choose your women?

39:56.733 --> 39:58.967
[Indistinct conversation
echoing]

39:59.000 --> 40:00.833
I know of no Khalil.

40:00.867 --> 40:04.400
[Chuckles]

40:04.433 --> 40:06.767
Thanks to your help,
we picked him up this week.

40:06.800 --> 40:09.100
My help?
He's upstairs.

40:11.400 --> 40:14.000
Shalom, Khalil.
[Chuckles]

40:14.033 --> 40:15.800
You don't have Khalil.

40:23.367 --> 40:27.067
**

40:27.100 --> 40:29.633
He is alive, for now.

40:29.667 --> 40:31.133
[Breathes shakily]

40:31.167 --> 40:32.333
When you've answered
my question,

40:32.367 --> 40:35.600
I might even let you
share his cell.

40:35.633 --> 40:37.333
Nurse him a bit.

40:37.367 --> 40:41.767
**

40:41.800 --> 40:43.533
[Sighs]

40:43.567 --> 40:46.800
You're on the diving board,
Salim.

40:46.833 --> 40:49.333
And the pool is empty.

40:49.367 --> 40:50.767
Come on, what have
you got for me

40:50.800 --> 40:52.833
so I can hold off my boss
for another night?

40:52.867 --> 40:55.400
That Mercedes --

40:55.433 --> 40:57.200
Where were you going
to drop it?

40:57.233 --> 41:04.200
**

41:06.333 --> 41:13.333
**

41:15.367 --> 41:16.700
Austria.

41:16.733 --> 41:18.300
Where in Austria?

41:18.333 --> 41:20.700
**

41:20.733 --> 41:24.200
Salzburg Train Station.
[Sobs]

41:24.233 --> 41:26.200
[Exhales deeply]

41:26.233 --> 41:30.100
Who was going to pick it up,
and when?

41:30.133 --> 41:34.967
I want to see Khalil.
[Sobs]

41:35.000 --> 41:38.667
**

41:38.700 --> 41:41.867
Here, a gift.

41:41.900 --> 41:43.767
Something I have
already given you.

41:43.800 --> 41:45.700
How can you give me something
you've already given me?

41:45.733 --> 41:48.867
[Indistinct conversations,
camera shutters clicking]

41:48.900 --> 41:50.300
Ah.

41:52.733 --> 41:54.200
Heavier this time.

41:57.400 --> 41:59.467
[Hinges click]

42:02.400 --> 42:05.033
Not exactly my taste.

42:05.067 --> 42:07.067
Good.
[Chuckles]

42:07.100 --> 42:09.567
It's your
actual response.

42:09.600 --> 42:13.167
We have to build this fiction
as solidly as possible.

42:13.200 --> 42:14.633
Is it real?

42:14.667 --> 42:16.433
Look beneath,
Charlie.

42:16.467 --> 42:18.567
There was something with it
in the box.

42:22.700 --> 42:25.733
You called the number --
my hotel.

42:25.767 --> 42:30.400
But you refused to meet me
anywhere but the theater.

42:30.433 --> 42:32.200
To return it.
It's too expensive.

42:32.233 --> 42:35.000
Yes. I'm too young to afford
something like that.

42:35.033 --> 42:37.433
[Chuckles]

42:37.467 --> 42:39.400
Sorry.

42:39.433 --> 42:40.800
[Chuckles]

42:40.833 --> 42:44.800
So, you arrived at the theater
after-hours.

42:44.833 --> 42:47.800
We met in the bar,
when everything had closed,

42:47.833 --> 42:50.300
in a corner.

42:50.333 --> 42:53.200
Behind you, I could see
the empty stage.

42:53.233 --> 42:56.600
You took the box
from your pocket,

42:56.633 --> 42:58.700
and you pushed it
across the table to me.

42:58.733 --> 43:05.433
**

43:05.467 --> 43:07.567
I need you to have it.
My Joan.

43:07.600 --> 43:09.967
[Chuckles]
I'm not a saint.

43:10.000 --> 43:13.000
People get crushes on actors
all the time.

43:13.033 --> 43:14.200
You're special.

43:14.233 --> 43:16.767
Yeah,
we're all special, love.

43:16.800 --> 43:20.233
No.
Just some of us.

43:20.267 --> 43:21.233
I am.

43:21.267 --> 43:22.500
[Chuckles]

43:22.533 --> 43:25.033
Which is why
I recognize it in you.

43:25.067 --> 43:27.400
[Sighs]

43:27.433 --> 43:28.600
[Chair creaks]

43:28.633 --> 43:31.400
**

43:31.433 --> 43:32.600
What are you doing?

43:32.633 --> 43:34.967
**

43:35.000 --> 43:36.167
Falling in love
with you.

43:36.200 --> 43:38.000
[Laughs]

43:38.033 --> 43:39.933
Infinitely.

43:39.967 --> 43:46.967
**

43:48.100 --> 43:55.100
**

43:56.200 --> 43:58.000
How much of this
is you?

43:58.033 --> 43:59.533
Is that
your one question?

43:59.567 --> 44:02.200
Mnnnnnh-mnh.

44:06.567 --> 44:09.233
Are you really
divorced?

44:09.267 --> 44:11.900
She couldn't
leave Jerusalem.

44:11.933 --> 44:13.100
I couldn't live
in Israel.

44:13.133 --> 44:15.033
Why?

44:15.067 --> 44:17.300
Not exactly my taste.

44:17.333 --> 44:18.900
Why?

44:18.933 --> 44:20.700
One question at a time.

44:20.733 --> 44:22.033
[Groans softly]

44:22.067 --> 44:24.700
So, does it play,
Charlie?

44:24.733 --> 44:26.700
Just about.

44:26.733 --> 44:29.133
Enough for me to take you
to dinner...

44:29.167 --> 44:31.133
in my hotel room?

44:31.167 --> 44:32.700
Cheeky bugger.

44:32.733 --> 44:37.100
[Birds crying]

44:37.133 --> 44:44.100
**

44:44.233 --> 44:51.233
**

44:51.333 --> 44:58.300
**

44:58.433 --> 45:00.000
[Glasses clink]

45:00.033 --> 45:01.400
[Ice rattles]

45:01.433 --> 45:08.400
**

45:10.600 --> 45:12.467
To the second night
of our honeymoon.

45:12.500 --> 45:14.667
[Glasses clink]

45:14.700 --> 45:16.267
[Glass clatters]

45:16.300 --> 45:18.567
You're only supposed to toast
if you're drinking, too.

45:18.600 --> 45:25.600
**

45:26.200 --> 45:33.200
**

45:33.800 --> 45:37.233
Where's all this
leading to, Jose?

45:37.267 --> 45:38.667
To bed.

45:38.700 --> 45:40.700
Great.
I love bed.

45:40.733 --> 45:45.833
**

45:45.867 --> 45:47.867
You're shy,
aren't you?

45:47.900 --> 45:49.133
[Becker scoffs]

45:49.167 --> 45:51.267
Becker: Michel has slept
with many women.

45:51.300 --> 45:53.300
**

45:53.333 --> 45:54.300
So?

45:54.333 --> 45:56.700
[Glass clatters]

45:56.733 --> 46:00.233
So, we fuck.

46:00.267 --> 46:01.433
Yeah, why not?

46:01.467 --> 46:02.800
[Snorts, giggles]

46:02.833 --> 46:05.133
Becker: Why not?
[Both laughing]

46:05.167 --> 46:07.133
How is he?

46:07.167 --> 46:09.000
Well, you tell me.

46:09.033 --> 46:10.500
Enthusiastic.

46:10.533 --> 46:13.300
**

46:13.333 --> 46:17.000
But he lacks technique.

46:17.033 --> 46:18.400
[Bag unzips]

46:18.433 --> 46:22.800
After we have sex,
we sleep...

46:22.833 --> 46:26.967
with this under the pillow,
always.

46:27.000 --> 46:29.100
I let you put a gun
under there?

46:29.133 --> 46:32.267
It thrills you.

46:32.300 --> 46:34.033
Really?

46:48.800 --> 46:52.100
[Exhales]

46:55.833 --> 46:58.333
Getting what you want puts you
in a bad mood, doesn't it?

46:58.367 --> 47:01.400
[Tape player clicks]

47:01.433 --> 47:02.933
Sleep.

47:02.967 --> 47:04.400
[Scoffs]

47:08.967 --> 47:12.467
Michel: With Al Nakba,
the British began a war

47:12.500 --> 47:15.533
for which they have not yet
been held to account.

47:15.567 --> 47:17.233
Becker: Al Nakba.

47:18.633 --> 47:22.433
[Lights flick]
Just as they dispersed
the people of Palestine,

47:22.467 --> 47:24.967
so shall we punish them
in their diaspora...
[Metal rattles]

47:25.000 --> 47:27.600
...and declare our agony
to the world.

47:32.933 --> 47:35.233
[Sighs]

47:35.267 --> 47:42.267
**

47:43.233 --> 47:50.200
**

47:51.200 --> 47:58.200
**

48:01.967 --> 48:04.167
A telegram for room 24.

48:04.200 --> 48:05.633
Oh.

48:15.400 --> 48:22.267
**

48:22.300 --> 48:24.367
[Coins jingle]

48:24.400 --> 48:27.967
[Coins rattle]

48:28.000 --> 48:31.467
[Rotary telephone dials]

48:31.500 --> 48:33.100
Becker:
She's not ready.

48:33.133 --> 48:35.067
Then get her ready,
Gadi.

48:35.100 --> 48:39.033
**

48:39.067 --> 48:42.633
[Dishes clanking,
indistinct conversations]

48:42.667 --> 48:46.133
**

48:46.167 --> 48:47.433
[Clears throat]

48:47.467 --> 48:49.567
-[Speaking indistinctly]
-Thank you.

48:49.600 --> 48:51.567
Forgive me.

48:51.600 --> 48:53.500
Frau Schulmann
was furious.

48:53.533 --> 48:56.267
[Chuckles]
Mm.

48:56.300 --> 48:57.433
We are on our way,
Paul.

48:57.467 --> 48:59.133
I can feel it
in my bones.

48:59.167 --> 49:01.500
I'll just need
one more favor

49:01.533 --> 49:04.233
from the Austrian
authorities now.
[Sighs]

49:04.267 --> 49:06.433
It was no small task
clearing the last shipment.

49:06.467 --> 49:12.200
And you will reap
no small rewards, I promise.

49:12.233 --> 49:15.900
You have an eye for detail,
Paul. We both know it.

49:15.933 --> 49:19.833
It was you who picked this
excellent cafÃ©, didn't you?

49:19.867 --> 49:23.233
[Forks clatter]

49:23.267 --> 49:27.867
Baumkuchen,
a German delicacy.

49:27.900 --> 49:31.433
It is, I think, the best
baumkuchen in all the country.

49:31.467 --> 49:32.500
Really?

49:36.733 --> 49:37.900
Hmm.

49:37.933 --> 49:41.300
[Chewing]

49:41.333 --> 49:43.200
A bit dry.

49:43.233 --> 49:45.833
For the best, you really
must go to Fussen.

49:45.867 --> 49:47.933
[Chuckles]
Details, Paul.

49:52.633 --> 49:54.000
I have more news.

49:54.033 --> 49:56.000
Hmm.

49:56.033 --> 49:57.300
Of Anna Witgen.

49:57.333 --> 50:00.967
The blonde bombshell.

50:01.000 --> 50:06.433
I tracked her movements
in the lead-up to the explosion.

50:06.467 --> 50:08.233
It turns out
she rented rooms --

50:08.267 --> 50:10.633
one night
in Maribor, Slovenia,

50:10.667 --> 50:12.767
and then she spent some time
in Salzburg

50:12.800 --> 50:16.367
before she came
to Bad Godesberg.

50:16.400 --> 50:18.200
Salzburg, Austria.

50:18.233 --> 50:20.933
Yes.

50:20.967 --> 50:22.833
The birthplace
of Mozart.

50:22.867 --> 50:24.633
**

50:24.667 --> 50:27.133
It can't be.

50:27.167 --> 50:32.133
These people never use
the same location twice.

50:32.167 --> 50:35.200
Alexis: Are you saying I've
been given false information?

50:35.233 --> 50:37.567
No, I have.

50:37.600 --> 50:41.567
The last favor
you asked me,

50:41.600 --> 50:43.967
it was so difficult
to help you.

50:44.000 --> 50:48.400
**

50:48.433 --> 50:49.600
I'm sorry.

50:49.633 --> 50:51.700
[Siren blares]

50:51.733 --> 50:58.533
**

50:58.567 --> 51:05.433
**

51:05.467 --> 51:09.967
The first night we spent
together in London,

51:10.000 --> 51:12.167
we made love.

51:12.200 --> 51:14.800
And I told you
my real name.

51:14.833 --> 51:19.533
It's not Michel.
Salim.

51:19.567 --> 51:21.100
A great secret.

51:21.133 --> 51:23.333
Why did you
tell me that?

51:23.367 --> 51:25.167
Because I trust you.

51:25.200 --> 51:29.333
**

51:29.367 --> 51:32.067
You will become
my latest recruit.

51:32.100 --> 51:34.867
And once you have
proven yourself,

51:34.900 --> 51:37.900
my network will
reach out to you,

51:37.933 --> 51:40.000
and you will enter
its ranks.

51:40.033 --> 51:45.867
**

51:45.900 --> 51:48.467
Enter its ranks?

51:48.500 --> 51:52.533
I will stay close to you,
every step of the way.

51:52.567 --> 51:55.567
[Indistinct conversation,
motorbike drives by]

51:55.600 --> 51:57.333
[Birds chirping]

51:57.367 --> 51:58.433
Your makeup.

51:58.467 --> 52:01.033
Oh!
Michel loves it.

52:01.067 --> 52:03.367
And he doesn't mind
me taking my time, either.

52:03.400 --> 52:05.833
-Really?
-Mm-hmm.

52:05.867 --> 52:07.933
Well, we might as well have
a little fun while we're at it.

52:07.967 --> 52:09.200
[Keys jingle]

52:12.133 --> 52:14.067
[Laughs] Ah.

52:14.100 --> 52:17.900
So, what happens now?

52:17.933 --> 52:21.433
Becker: First, I set you
a very important test.

52:21.467 --> 52:22.900
Mm-hmm.

52:22.933 --> 52:27.033
To pass, you must drive this car
for the next 800 miles,

52:27.067 --> 52:28.733
all the way across
the Yugoslav border

52:28.767 --> 52:29.933
and into Austria.

52:29.967 --> 52:31.100
[Chuckles]

52:31.133 --> 52:32.800
Great.

52:32.833 --> 52:34.400
I've never been
to Austria before.

52:34.433 --> 52:36.000
Alone.

52:36.033 --> 52:38.433
**

52:38.467 --> 52:40.500
You said
you'd be close!

52:40.533 --> 52:44.000
I will be,
but not in the car.

52:44.033 --> 52:46.000
And once you reach
Salzburg Train Station,

52:46.033 --> 52:47.533
I'll find you again.

52:47.567 --> 52:50.433
Hmm.

52:50.467 --> 52:52.233
But there's
one more thing.

52:52.267 --> 52:53.467
Of course.

52:53.500 --> 52:56.667
**

52:56.700 --> 52:58.200
Turn right at the end.

52:58.233 --> 53:04.700
**

53:04.733 --> 53:11.200
**

53:11.233 --> 53:17.600
**

53:17.633 --> 53:20.000
[Seatbelt unbuckles, door opens]

53:20.033 --> 53:26.033
**

53:26.067 --> 53:32.167
**

53:32.200 --> 53:35.000
From here,
you'll be driving that car.

53:35.033 --> 53:37.133
What's the difference?

53:37.167 --> 53:39.033
There's just papers
in there, love.

53:39.067 --> 53:40.733
Nothing sinister.

53:40.767 --> 53:44.367
The point is, you've promised
to do this for Michel here.

53:44.400 --> 53:47.533
Now, if there's any trouble,
you're on your own.

53:47.567 --> 53:48.933
[Keys rattle]

53:48.967 --> 53:51.367
**

53:51.400 --> 53:55.133
It's Russian semtex,
divided into bricks...

53:55.167 --> 53:56.267
Gadi!

53:56.300 --> 53:57.933
...hidden
in the interior panel.

53:57.967 --> 54:01.767
Enough for
a dozen bombs.

54:01.800 --> 54:03.200
Is this real?

54:03.233 --> 54:05.233
It's real.

54:05.267 --> 54:07.000
**

54:07.033 --> 54:08.933
What are you gonna
use it for?

54:08.967 --> 54:13.300
To kill Jews
throughout Europe.

54:13.333 --> 54:16.800
And just as they dispersed
the people of Palestine,

54:16.833 --> 54:18.900
so shall we punish them
in their diaspora

54:18.933 --> 54:20.933
and declare our agony
to the world.

54:20.967 --> 54:23.367
**

54:23.400 --> 54:25.967
I ask you to do this,
Charlie.

54:26.000 --> 54:28.700
**

54:28.733 --> 54:30.767
For me.

54:30.800 --> 54:33.533
For love.

54:33.567 --> 54:37.333
For our great
revolution.

54:37.367 --> 54:40.533
To prove that you are
as special as I believe.

54:40.567 --> 54:43.800
**

54:43.833 --> 54:47.767
This is your debut
in the theater of the real.

54:47.800 --> 54:54.800
**

54:56.233 --> 55:03.233
**

55:03.600 --> 55:10.600
**

55:11.000 --> 55:18.000
**

55:18.400 --> 55:25.400
**
